# PDF to Revit Conversion Skill

## Overview
This skill provides the complete workflow for converting PDF floor plans into Revit models using the floor-plan-vision MCP and RevitMCPBridge.

## When to Use
- Converting architectural PDF drawings to BIM
- Extracting wall/door/window data from floor plans
- Automating model creation from design documents

## Complete Pipeline

### Phase 1: PDF Analysis
```
1. mcp__floor-plan-vision__get_pdf_info(pdf_path)
   → Get page count, dimensions

2. mcp__floor-plan-vision__get_floor_plan_pages(pdf_path)
   → Identify which pages are floor plans

3. mcp__floor-plan-vision__extract_geometry(pdf_path, page_num)
   → Get all vector data (lines, arcs, text)
```

### Phase 2: Element Detection
```
4. mcp__floor-plan-vision__detect_walls(geometry)
   → Find wall segments from geometry

5. mcp__floor-plan-vision__classify_walls(walls)
   → Exterior vs interior classification

6. mcp__floor-plan-vision__detect_doors(geometry, walls)
   → Find door locations

7. mcp__floor-plan-vision__detect_windows(geometry, walls)
   → Find window locations

8. mcp__floor-plan-vision__extract_text(geometry)
   → Room names, dimensions, labels
```

### Phase 3: Scale & Coordinate Normalization
```
9. mcp__floor-plan-vision__detect_scale(geometry)
   → Auto-detect drawing scale (1/4"=1'-0", etc.)

10. mcp__floor-plan-vision__normalize_coordinates(geometry)
    → Set building origin, normalize to feet

11. mcp__floor-plan-vision__get_grid_dimensions(pdf_path)
    → Extract structural grid spacing
```

### Phase 4: Validation
```
12. mcp__floor-plan-vision__validate_detection(walls, doors, windows)
    → Confidence scores, completeness check

13. mcp__floor-plan-vision__connect_walls(walls)
    → Build continuous wall chains
```

### Phase 5: Revit Spec Generation
```
14. mcp__floor-plan-vision__build_revit_spec(walls, doors, windows, text, scale)
    → Generate JSON spec for Revit placement
```

### Phase 6: Model Creation (RevitMCPBridge)
```
15. Query available types in target Revit project
16. Map detected elements to available types
17. Create walls segment by segment
18. Place doors and windows
19. Validate placement vs PDF
```

## Quick Analysis (Single Call)
```
mcp__floor-plan-vision__analyze_floor_plan(
  pdf_path="/path/to/floor-plan.pdf",
  page_num=0,
  detect_all=false,  // true for fixtures, furniture
  scale="auto"       // or specify like "1/4\" = 1'-0\""
)
```

## Scale Detection

### Common Scales
| Scale | 1" on paper = | 1' on paper = |
|-------|---------------|---------------|
| 1/8" = 1'-0" | 8 feet | 0.125" |
| 1/4" = 1'-0" | 4 feet | 0.25" |
| 3/8" = 1'-0" | 2.67 feet | 0.375" |
| 1/2" = 1'-0" | 2 feet | 0.5" |
| 1" = 1'-0" | 1 foot | 1" |

### Scale Detection Methods
1. Look for scale text in title block
2. Find dimension strings and compare to drawn length
3. Use door width (typically 3'-0") as reference
4. Check grid spacing (often 20', 25', or 30')

## Coordinate Handling

### PDF Coordinates
- Origin at bottom-left of page
- Units: points (72 points = 1 inch)
- Y increases upward

### Revit Coordinates
- Origin typically at Grid 1/A intersection
- Units: feet (internal)
- Y increases northward

### Conversion Formula
```python
# PDF points to Revit feet
revit_x = (pdf_x - origin_x) * scale_factor / 72.0
revit_y = (pdf_y - origin_y) * scale_factor / 72.0

# scale_factor depends on drawing scale
# For 1/4" = 1'-0": scale_factor = 48 (4 feet per inch)
```

## Wall Detection Heuristics

### Identifying Walls
- Parallel line pairs 4"-12" apart
- Continuous runs without gaps
- Thicker line weight than details
- Form closed or semi-closed shapes

### Exterior vs Interior
- Exterior: Forms convex hull of building
- Interior: Everything else
- Also consider: wall thickness, insulation patterns

## Common Challenges

### Multi-scale Drawings
- Detail views at different scales on same page
- Solution: Detect view boundaries, process separately

### Curved Walls
- Arcs must be converted to polylines
- Use appropriate segment count for accuracy

### Missing Data
- Doors shown as breaks in walls
- Windows may not have swing lines
- Use room labels to infer door locations

## Quality Checklist

### Before Conversion
- [ ] PDF is vector-based (not scanned image)
- [ ] Drawing scale is known or detectable
- [ ] Target Revit project has needed families
- [ ] Level heights defined

### After Detection
- [ ] Wall count seems reasonable
- [ ] Exterior walls form closed perimeter
- [ ] Door count matches room count roughly
- [ ] Dimensions match scale text

### After Revit Placement
- [ ] Model matches PDF visually
- [ ] No overlapping walls
- [ ] All doors/windows hosted
- [ ] Room boundaries closed

## Error Handling

### PDF Issues
| Problem | Detection | Solution |
|---------|-----------|----------|
| Raster PDF | No geometry extracted | Use OCR/image processing |
| Wrong page | No walls found | Try different page |
| Corrupted | Read error | Try PDF repair tool |

### Detection Issues
| Problem | Cause | Solution |
|---------|-------|----------|
| Too many walls | Picking up detail lines | Filter by line weight |
| Missing walls | Light line weight | Lower detection threshold |
| Wrong scale | Scale not detected | Specify manually |

### Placement Issues
| Problem | Cause | Solution |
|---------|-------|----------|
| Offset location | Origin mismatch | Adjust coordinate transform |
| Wrong size | Scale error | Recalculate scale factor |
| Missing types | Family not loaded | Load or map to available |
